640 static inline uint8_t* HSIHeader_getPayload (HSIHeader* ptrHeader)
641 {
642  /* Convert the header size into bytes. Skip the header to get the payload */
643  return (uint8_t*)ptrHeader + HSIHeader_toBytes(ptrHeader->sdkHeader.headerSize);
644 }

680 static inline uint16_t HSIHeader_getPaddingSize (HSIHeader* ptrHeader)
681 {
682  uint16_t minHeaderSize;
683 
684  /* Mandatory Size of the Header: Size of the header without any padding. */
685  minHeaderSize = sizeof (HSIDataCardHeader) + sizeof(HSISDKHeader);
686  minHeaderSize = HSIHeader_toCBUFFUnits (minHeaderSize);
687 
688  /* What ever is left after the mandatory header is the padding */
689  return (ptrHeader->sdkHeader.headerSize - minHeaderSize);
690 }

714 static inline void HSIHeader_getVersion
715 (
716  HSIHeader* ptrHeader,
717  uint8_t* major,
718  uint8_t* minor,
719  uint8_t* bugFix,
720  uint8_t* build
721 )
722 {
723  uint16_t version = HSIHeader_htons (ptrHeader->sdkHeader.version);
724 
725  *major = (version & 0xE00) >> 9;
726  *minor = (version & 0x1C0) >> 6;
727  *bugFix = (version & 0x031) >> 3;
728  *build = (version & 0x7);
729 }

746 static inline uint32_t HSIHeader_getTotalLength (HSIHeader* ptrHeader)
747 {
748  uint32_t totalLength;
749 
750  totalLength = sizeof(HSIDataCardHeader);
751  totalLength += (((HSIHeader_htons(ptrHeader->dataCardHeader.totalLengthMSW) & 0xFFF) << 12U) |
752  (HSIHeader_htons(ptrHeader->dataCardHeader.totalLengthLSW) & 0xFFF));
753  return totalLength;
754 }

HSI_HEADER_MAX_CQ
#define HSI_HEADER_MAX_CQ
This is the maximum number of chirp quality which can be supported in the HSI Header. This should be the same as the definition supported in the ADCBUF Driver. However we cannot use the same macro here because it will make the file dependent on the mmWave SDK. So instead we redefine the macro and verify the sanity during the HSI Header initialization.
